title: As the world inches back to a pre-WW2 order, the 'middle powers' face a grave new challenge
summary_full: With economic stagnation and extremes of inequality comes corrosion of trust in democratic institutions. So Trump may be a symptom, not a cause, of what Carney called a "rupture" with the post-WW2 order.
